.TH "nfsacl_encode" 9 "nfsacl_encode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfsacl_encode \- Encode an NFSv3 ACL
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfsacl_encode
.BI "(struct xdr_buf *buf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int base "  ","
.BI "struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct posix_acl *acl "  ","
.BI "int encode_entries "  ","
.BI "int typeflag "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
destination xdr_buf to contain XDR encoded ACL
.IP "base" 12
byte offset in xdr_buf where XDR'd ACL begins
.IP "inode" 12
inode of file whose ACL this is
.IP "acl" 12
posix_acl to encode
.IP "encode_entries" 12
whether to encode ACEs as well
.IP "typeflag" 12
ACL type: NFS_ACL_DEFAULT or zero
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns size of encoded ACL in bytes or a negative errno value.
